 {"id":"bd-kgxda","title":"Implement SELECT without FROM in VDBE codegen","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-27T11:05:58.878878685Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-27T11:06:18.074430606Z","closed_at":"2026-02-27T11:06:18.074412241Z","close_reason":"SELECT without FROM in VDBE codegen — 5 new tests, 1214 total passing","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":1808,"issue_id":"bd-kgxda","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"## Implement SELECT without FROM in VDBE Codegen

### Problem
SELECT statements without a FROM clause (e.g. `SELECT 1`, `SELECT 1+2`,
`SELECT abs(-5)`, `SELECT typeof(3.14)`) failed in the VDBE codegen path
with `CodegenError::Unsupported("SELECT without FROM")`. These queries fell
through to the connection.rs fallback interpreter path.

### Fix
Added `codegen_select_without_from()` function that generates a minimal
VDBE program: `Init -> Transaction -> [eval exprs] -> ResultRow -> Halt`.

- Evaluates each result column via `emit_expr` with `ctx=None` (no table)
- Supports WHERE clause filtering (e.g. `SELECT 1 WHERE 0` returns 0 rows)
- Star/TableStar result columns emit NULL (no table to expand)
- No table cursor needed — no OpenRead/Rewind/Next loop

### Files Changed
- `crates/fsqlite-vdbe/src/codegen.rs` — Added `codegen_select_without_from`,
  early return in `codegen_select` before FROM clause lookup
- `crates/fsqlite-core/src/connection.rs` — 5 new tests

### Tests (5 new, all pass)
- `test_select_without_from_function_call` — abs(-42), length('hello')
- `test_select_without_from_null_and_typeof` — NULL, typeof(NULL)
- `test_select_without_from_where_false` — SELECT 1 WHERE 0 returns 0 rows
- `test_select_without_from_where_null` — SELECT 1 WHERE NULL returns 0 rows
- `test_select_without_from_case_expression` — CASE WHEN expression

### Quality Gates
- 1214 fsqlite-core tests pass (0 regressions, +5 new)
- Clippy clean (pedantic+nursery), fmt clean
